markdown# Machine Learning for Real-World Data Analytics: Real Estate Valuation

## 1. Project Overview
This repository contains an end-to-end supervised machine learning regression pipeline designed to automate residential real estate property evaluations. The project uses structural home features (bedrooms, bathrooms, and land area acreage) to predict market pricing in USD ($). 

### Key Results
* **Linear Regression R² Score:** 0.9643 (Selected Optimal System Model)
* **Random Forest R² Score:** 0.9371

---

## 2. Repository Architecture Workflow
Raw CSV Generation -> StandardScaler Transform -> Train/Test Partition (80/20) -> Grid Search Optimization -> Performance Metrics Log -> Evaluation PNG Generation

---

## 3. Software Requirements & Dependencies
This system runs on Python 3.10 or higher.
* pandas
* numpy
* scikit-learn
* matplotlib
* seaborn

---

## 4. Instructions to Reproduce Results
1. Open your terminal or Anaconda Prompt.
2. Navigate to this folder: cd real-estate-analytics
3. Install package dependencies: pip install -r requirements.txt
4. Run the main execution pipeline: python src/main.py
